The '''black-headed parrotbill''' ('''''Paradoxornis margaritae''''') is a [[bird]] [[species]] often placed with the [[Old World babbler]]s ([[Family (taxonomy)|family]] Timaliidae) or in the [[Sylviidae]], but it actually seems to belong to the distinct family [[Paradoxornithidae]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Sylviid babblers, parrotbills, white-eyes – IOC World Bird List |url=https://www.worldbirdnames.org/new/bow/sylvias/ |access-date=2022-06-04 |language=en-US}}</ref>

It is found in eastern [[Cambodia]] and southern [[Vietnam]]. Its natural [[habitat]] is subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]]s.

